[2]
Date: Thu, 13 Jan 2000 11:40:19 +0100
From: leitritz@m3401.mpk.med.uni-muenchen.de
Via: Wolfgang Preiser <W.Preiser@em.uni-frankfurt.de>
Source: Pressemitteilungen (press release) des Robert Koch-Instituts
<RKI_PRESSEDIENST@LISTSERV.GMD.DE>

Further update - RKI press release - imported Lassa fever - Germany
Wed, 12 Jan 2000 19:19:17 +0100
Suspicion of Lassa fever confirmed (Update)
The 23-year old female German student who is currently being treated
for Lassa fever in the Mission Hospital in Wuerzburg arrived in
Germany, according to latest information, not on New Year's eve but on
7 Jan 2000, probably through Frankfurt Rhein-Main airport.
According to further information she spent the night of 6-7 Jan 2000 in
a still unknown hotel in Lisbon, Portugal [now doubtful -- see [3]
below - Mod.JW], and had already fallen ill with high fever in Cote
d'Ivoire (Ivory Coast) on 2 January 2000. She had not taken malaria
prophylaxis. Two yellow fever vaccinations had apparently been done
in time before the trip.
It is still unclear whether the patient had returned from Abidjan (Ivory
Coast) or Ouagadougou (Burkina Faso) to Europe. As she had
apparently fallen ill before her departure from Africa, a potential risk to
fellow travellers on the plane cannot be excluded with certainty. At
present the flights she used from Ouagadougou or Abidjan and from
Lisbon are being traced [these are reported below - Mod.JW].
--
Edgar Muschketat
Robert Koch-Institu
